                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-1435" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH COX</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in Mr. Topley's shop on the 27th of October —the policeman came in, and asked the prisoner if he was master of the shop—he said he was—the policeman asked him if he had served any Per<lb></lb>son that morning with more than lib. of coffee—he said yes he bad served a young man with 2 1/2 lb. of coffee, a bottle of ginger wine, some bacon and sugar, and the policeman said he had not got the sugar when he was stopped.</p>
